{"ts":"2026-06-07T10:03:51.603Z","author":"audit-platform-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-7u9j"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"Add narrow pm_append MCP tool for agent log-seeding without pm_run passthrough"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"pm_run action='append' routes through the generic catch-all handler with no top-level schema. Agents that want to seed a body or log entry into an existing item must pass all options inside `options: {}`. A narrow pm_append tool would surface `id` and `options` at the top level (like pm_comments, pm_notes), participate in the unexpected-key warning system (pm-qxwu), and be self-documenting in tools/list. Append is a frequent agent operation — closing a task often involves adding evidence before close."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Feature"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":3},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["agent-ux","area:mcp","dx"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-06-07T10:03:51.603Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-06-07T10:03:51.603Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"audit-platform-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-5k4v"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/risk","value":"low"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/confidence","value":"high"}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"4bab85dcd12d02f5afb066708febd7ccc4b7f2b2ecd8d8292fcbfb69f512c352","message":""}
{"ts":"2026-06-07T10:22:12.156Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"update","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-06-07T10:22:12.156Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/acceptance_criteria","value":"- Narrow `pm_append` MCP tool exists, mapping to `pm append`\n- Registered in PM_TOOL_ACTIONS + tool schema/parameter contracts\n- Compact-by-default output; covered by MCP tool-list test\n- docs/AGENT_GUIDE MCP tool table updated"}],"before_hash":"4bab85dcd12d02f5afb066708febd7ccc4b7f2b2ecd8d8292fcbfb69f512c352","after_hash":"84700141726a51d378aab02a2ceaa586ba5002fb0c653ee6c68e5d2db7768163","message":"Add structured acceptance_criteria (best-practice consistency)"}
{"ts":"2026-06-10T14:46:27.069Z","author":"mcp-tools-agent","op":"claim","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-06-10T14:46:27.069Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/assignee","value":"mcp-tools-agent"}],"before_hash":"84700141726a51d378aab02a2ceaa586ba5002fb0c653ee6c68e5d2db7768163","after_hash":"541d143327f1be5778237981d0f1363cb4179d4f5e72271a74bc6d5f7ce19cef"}
{"ts":"2026-06-10T15:13:43.022Z","author":"mcp-tools-agent","op":"comment_add","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-06-10T15:13:43.022Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/comments","value":[{"created_at":"2026-06-10T15:13:43.022Z","author":"mcp-tools-agent","text":"Implemented narrow pm_append MCP tool mapping to pm append: id (required) + body + fullChangedFields + options top-level, like pm_comments/pm_notes. body is hoisted into options in optionsWithAuthor (action=append) so runAppend receives it; options.body still wins on conflict. Output is compact by default via the existing withMutationCompaction path (changed_field_count instead of changed_fields). Participates in the unexpected-key warning system; advertised in server instructions (and removed append from the pm_run-only action enumeration there). Verified end-to-end in the handshake spec: append via top-level body, no warnings, changed_field_count=1, body visible via pm_get depth=full."}]}],"before_hash":"541d143327f1be5778237981d0f1363cb4179d4f5e72271a74bc6d5f7ce19cef","after_hash":"a8fe4ab1f793ccc6cdcac95d8ee37a43781f2e8d9506ca67a3163b1d8b18bd60"}
